reviews.text: Definitely a must do for anyone but especially Hemingway fans. Tour guides were friendly and entertaining. Plenty of fun facts (stories). If you hang out after on the grounds you can listen in to the other guides and hear their spin on the tales. Some of the cats are very friendly. Told not to pick them up but twice we came across people sitting on a bench with a cat in their lap and a look on their face that said "I didn't pick it up, it just climbed up on me". Very fun!

I enjoyed the tour. After viewing, I pondered at the thought of how lovely that area would have been before it was popular. Museum was short and sweet Will likely visit again with others. Some have commented about the odor- It's an old unoccupied house in a moist climate and there are cats so it's not "spring fresh." If you have a cat allergy be aware, otherwise, stop in.

Love, love, loved visiting this house! Such a beautiful house and cute cats every where! My family and I luckily went on day that wasn't full so we didn't have to wait in line. I can't not remember our tour guides name, he was a older man but he was awesome and funny. I think my favorite Hemingway story would have to be about the swimming pool and penny. My kids were loving on the cats and you can definitely tell the cats like the attention, it was neat seeing some with 6 toes. Hemingway's "man cave" was neat as well. Planning on visiting again. 3/9/19

Overall a very worthwhile visit.  Chris, our tour guide, was enthusiastic and shared so many pieces of information about Hemingway and his life.  Cats were elusive but when seen were majestic. The landscaping was beautiful.  The photographs on the walls took you back in time. It makes me want to read and reread everyone of Hemingway’s books.

One tour guide, Sarah, was rude to me as I was sitting down close to a cat watering hole.  She told me I had to move because she had a tour.  There are dozens and dozens of people milling around ALL OVER that weren’t on tours.  It’s just something you need to be able to flow with.  To contrast, our guide wasn’t phased at all when people walked through our group; he continued with his discussion as if it didn’t happen.  An example of a true professional.

So enjoyed walking the veranda at the Hemingway house!! The kitty's were present everywhere! My son was able to pet several! A wonderful step back in time!! If anyone is interested in beautiful plants and cool greenery you can sit on several of the benches on the grounds!They do have tours available if you chose to go on them included with your admission fee!!

A nicely detailed tour of the house and a complimentary bottle of water!   Almost all of the furniture in the house was used by President Truman including a custom made poker table.   The tour guide was very knowledgeable.  No photos or videos are allowed in the house. Also no outside drinks.

Awesome little place. They refused to sell it to us and remove the building blocking the view of the ocean. I would not do what we did and take 2 infants and a toddler into this place. Our 3 year old did quite well though. Lots to see and learn.

Beautiful, peaceful grounds. Great tour. "Bill" our guide was informative and funny. Would def. recommend. Suggest being at the end of the group. Gives you extra time to look around at each stage of the tour while others migrate to the next room. Even history buffs should be prepared to learn something!
Lovely walk and we stopped here for postcards for family. Beautiful area full of very interesting history beside our resort. Worth the stroll!

A slice of history and an unforgettable experience. You get a outstanding tour of the interior. Everyone is there to make your visit exceptional. They have a nice gift shop for one of a kind souvenirs. No pictures inside so you have to see to believe.

Great place to take the family or an atypical experience to learn more about the keys and surrounding waters. The building is architecturally awesome and exhibits were well put together. Awesome deal for locals on the first Sunday!

great museum that blends art and history. Learned lots of cool things about the keys that made our whole vacation more enjoyable. Well worth the price. $12 adults, $5 students (no ID required). We are 4 guys in their 20s and my friends aren't really interested in learning anything or reading and don't really care about art or history, but they loved it. That's how engaging it is.

Wonderful art exhibition and history museum in key west. The current exhibits are a blend of art and history, including a large set of pieces based on the old man and the sea by Hemingway. Check it out if you have time!

We loved all of the history and art inside and outside. This place gives you so much information. We were only here for the day, so we couldn't spend a bunch of time here, but the time we were, was enjoyable. The figures on the outside are creepy and cool.
Key West history, very cool perspective. The Old Man and the Sea illustrations going up the stairs are spectacular.
Great place to stay in Key West! The hotel is very clean and they have excellent breakfast too! We would definitely stay there again!
Good location.  Comfortable room and bed.  No frills, very nice and quiet.  Easy access to everything on the island.  Recommended for a couple's getaway.

The Hemingway suite was beautiful, spacious and the perfect escape from the Key West heat. It was nice to have so much space, working kitchen, and a little privacy. My favorite view was through the ceiling high windows toward the lighthouse.

Return visit for us.  Stay in The Hemingway Suite for a kitchen and living room as well as washer and dryer too.  Great location too right next to The Lighthouse and across the street from Hemingway House.  Convenient walk to great restaurants and shopping but more quiet than a busy street.

The Lighthouse Court Hotel was wonderful to stay at! Myself and 3 other adults stayed for three nights and we all loved it. We were in their biggest bungalow and it was comfortable for all of us. The room had 2 queen beds, fridge, microwave, drawers, 2 chairs, and small table. The bathroom includes a hairdryer. Everything was clean and we did not have any issues with stuff not working. They have a much-appreciated complimentary breakfast 8am-10am with cereal, 2% milk, yogurt, bagels, toast, hard boiled eggs, oranges, bananas, coffee, tea, orange juice, and water. They have these nice trays and plates for guests to use and it was wonderful having breakfast by the poolside each morning. We had some early mornings so it might've been nice for breakfast to start a little sooner, say 7:30 or so, but they had a good variety of food. The pool is not heated, but the sun keeps it plenty warm. It's very clean and they provide pool towels. All the grounds we're very well maintained and the hotel is nicely nestled into the foliage. Everyone that worked there was very nice and accommodating, other than the roosters that woke us up at 4am every day. Thanks for the great stay!

Its is a marker at the place but little else as in there in no shade to stand under also. Queues can be long just to click a picture with it and temperatures high. Strongly suggest carrying floppy hats or umbrella to be able to bear both.

A shade for people to stand under to escape under would be nice. A small plaque to explain more tell a story would be great

It's neat! There can definitely be a long line depending what time you go. It seems like early morning is the best time. Just snap a pic and go! Most people are willing to take a picture for you if you just ask. :) If you are in Key West, this is surely a picture spot you do not want to miss.

It is an amazing landmark 'point' (no pun intended), but point it is; and overcrowded for no proper reason. Folks tend to spend so much time just for that one shot. 

So if you want to stay on that line, be prepared to spend some time. Or just be smart and click from the front side, if you do not have any issue having a stranger in the background. :)

This is a neat land mark to visit for a photo op especially if you are in any of the Florida Keys for a couple of days. Not worth the drive if you are only there for one day. Parking is a challenge because the area around it is neighborhoods requiring permits to park. It might be best to taxi , walk or bike in. It is a 5 to 15 minute wait just for the photo opportunity. Local vendors are nearby selling coconut drinks.

I am not sure how I actually feel about this.
It's just a landmark of the southernmost point. That's all it is! There is a huge line(why?no idea!)depending on the time and season you are here.My trip here ended up being sort of anti climatic.
I had fun in Key west,no doubt there! had good food,good view of the ocean,but I could have done that in Miami too or Long key.
If you are in Florida for a short period,you can skip Key west,I promise you are not missing much.

Great time there during happy hour. Great way to meet new people. their prices are pretty reasonable, and the food is very good. I highly recommend sitting outside so that you can watch the boats, and it's easier to meet new people there. There's hosted seating inside, but not outside. So you can generally get people to share a table with you. We met some really interesting and fun people that way.

A very friendly atmosphere can a large restaurant. Live music, on the water on two sides. Four stars because the portions were rather small. The beer was cold. The margaritas were sweet, we don't care for sweet margaritas. So from a personal point of view 3 stars.

The lasting impression here was the live music was very good. 

Food was decent and the views of the nearby boats was very nice. A peaceful type atmosphere. 

There were fish to feed at the dock and it made my smile to see so many families enjoying their time. 

They also have a large gift shop if that is your thing.
Amazing Pink Royal Key West Shrimp.  Not on menu. Need to ask.  Worth every penny.  Drenched in melted butter they taste like lobster.  My husband and I ate 1 pound then ordered another.

Really good food.  Great salad with very tasteful portion of snapper on top.  The snapper fish sandwich was one of the best I had on this trip!   The calamari was very lightly breaded and very flavorful!

So you can generally get people to share a table with you. We met some really interesting and fun people that way.

They also have a large gift shop if that is your thing.

Really good food.  Great salad with very tasteful portion of snapper on top.  The snapper fish sandwich was one of the best I had on this trip!   The calamari was very lightly breaded and very flavorful!

The atmosphere was vibrant and fun! The food was amazing! The drinks were good too! We were talking with people from the bar and having a great time. If you get a chance to swing in, I would recommend it!
The service was a little slow,  even though they weren't busy.  We still had fun! Good Key lime pie. Worth the stop. We enjoyed ourselves! 2 for 1 drinks,  ya gotta go at least once!
Cool decor. Preciseley what I expected. Perfect for lunch. I went for the Cuban Burger over the expected Cheeseburger in Paradise. Courteous staff. Stellar service!
One order, a burger, had to be sent back due to not cooked correctly. The jambalaya had little flavor.  Manager and waitress were both very good.

This is a nice bar with atmosphere to match. We were there a little before noon and it was almost full. A must stop in Key West. Ordered  sandwiches that were both very good. Make sure to order a "5 o'clock some where" if you go, it is an awesome drink.

The food was okay. I am no fish expert but the fish tasted frozen vs fresh to me. The seasoning was tasty, but salty. The service however was spectacular.  Jose our waiter was friendly and attentive. The decor  of the restaurant was really nice and the location was great with the live music.

I was looking for traditional Cuban food and was very impressed with this place!!!!! Scenic, friendly and cute decor for photo opportunities. I had a meat dish with beans, rice and THE BEST plantains!!!!! Our server was very personable and prompt. I will recommend this place to many 😀

Great good + great waiter = a wonderful dinner lasting two + hours!  Classic Cuba  cuisine with a lot of nice touches..
Large portions are the norm

Cuban touches are all around..
Strong  coffee, plantains, Cuban beverages. Music at night during dinner

A lot of families enjoying their dinner together on a Sundsy evening.

Reasonably priced as well!

the place is very cozy, the service is fine, but the food has a lot to improve especially for the prices. for visitors from other countries this is the best Cuban food they have eaten. But for local people like me who know these typical dishes of Cuba, there is still a lot to improve in flavor and quality.

We absolutely love this place and have cocktails every sunset at the bar right there on Mallory Square. Staff was just fantastic the appetizers are also very good. They have live music every evening as well which makes the environment even more fun.

My favorite place to eat (and drink) in Key west! I have been coming here for over 30 years now and, even though everything has over-commercialized around them, each time I come here it brings me back to the good old days in South Florida! Best oysters and shrimp for miles! Fresh and tasty! I usually stumble in here for happy hour (4:30 -6:30 Daily) when all my favorites are around 1/2 price (including beer) and consistently have a great time! If you're traveling south to Key West and you enjoy fresh oysters and shrimp, be sure to check this place out!

If you're coming in to Key West and you don't stop at Half Shell Raw Bar you're definitely doing your vacation wrong! This place is hands-down one of my favorite stops we had on our trip, the oysters with garlic butter were outstanding, and the stone crab is so yummy!!
The service staff is pleasant, very helpful and answers every question you have with a smile which for me is 50% of the reason why I go back to some place! I really appreciate that a lot!
By the way in case you didn't know if you sit near the dock you're able to look down into the water and watch lots of fish swim by including some enormous tarpon that come to visit! It's almost being at an aquarium right at lunch!
Awesome seafood. Fresh oysters and fish. You can not go wrong. My girl started eating raw oysters here and loved them. Thanks

Prices are not bad but your meal may add up depending on what you are into. The mixed drinks are pretty good. I am a fan of the rum buckets. Also, the atmosphere alone makes this a top spot on my list while in Key West.

Best oysters in Key West...
     If you go during happy hour best prices too! Buffalo shrimp, oysters, and calamari are great and super-fresh.
     Drink specials and HH rock here as well. Really all that said, I pretty much go here for oysters, buff shrimp and finish up somewhere else. Nice view from patio as well 👌.

I accidentally tripped on this place while waiting for friends to get into town. Great menu, great wine, outdoor seating if you want or indoor to get away from the humidity if you need. I ordered the homemade spinach & ricotta ravioli, and the half size was a perfect lunch portion. The prices may scare you a bit, but well worth it - just remember You Are On VACATION! ENJOY!!!
Busy night life.  Food was good.. fairly loud. We were upstairs which maybe a little more calm.  Nice setting open air tables. Tables little  too busy for me. But not crazy

What a memorable dinner. Service was very attentive, friendly, and helpful. Porch seating was just lovely in perfect weather. The place was homely and welcoming. Had the arugula and pecorino salad to start with our cocktails - fabulous. Generous portion for sharing and loved the flavors. My boyfriend had the snapper on squid ink fettuccine and I had the half portion of lobster ravioli (which was perfect portion for me) and both were just fabulous. The pasta was unforgettable. Texture just perfect - you knew it was fresh! Would love to come back here next time we are in town.

The Grouper Ceviche was memorably delicious! Super fresh, tender and delicately seasoned to perfection. My husband equally enjoyed his fish tacos. The service was casual and spot on. Sitting outside under the covered porch with a well made drink and five star food...bliss!
We ate here for dinner and it is a great location for people watching. The outdoor deck was very nice and the service was very good. Had a good meal and the drink list was quite good.

Vegan carrot cake to die for! They have a great choice of delicious vegetarian and vegan meals and as I said their vegan carrot cake is over the top delicious. My omnivore family also loved their food. Very friendly waitress as well. Definitely the best restaurant on key west.

Recently changed ownership and name to Ocean Grill and is wonderful. Fantastic  brunch with bottomless Mimosas. Every thing about this place is great. From the excellent food and drinks to the knowledgeable and friendly staff and reasonabe prices this is definitely worth visiting.
Really cool place. Yummy Sangria and great happy hour deals on drinks and food. Had the calamari which was super yummy and spicy. Great place!
Start your bar crawl here! Great happy hour 5-7pm, on both food and crafted cocktails. Nice upscale casual atmosphere and friendly service. Perfect base for a night out.

First Dinner in Key West the night we got there and it was worth every second of it. They have the most delicious cucumber, basil Martini-yum! I had the mussel in sauce with coconut rice and sent back a clean plate. More than that the owner is very vested in his customers and took the time to welcome those coming in and customers leaving. We had a question about the magnificent painting on the wall inside and watching him light up as he told us the historic significance was a sheer delight. A star each for the food, location, ambiance, staff, and above/beyond owner engagement.
